question: Find institutions from the region of Nordjylland
query:
SELECT T1.institutions_name
FROM institutions AS T1
         JOIN eu_territorial_units AS T2 ON T1.geocode_regions_3 = T2.geocode_regions
WHERE T2.description = 'Nordjylland'

question: Find the name of principal investigators in projects that started in 2014
query:
SELECT T2.full_name
FROM projects AS T1 join people as T2 on T1.principal_investigator = T2.unics_id
WHERE T1.start_year = 2014

question: Show the full name of people being investigators in projects that began in 2014
query:

FROM projects AS T1 join people as T2 on T1.principal_investigator = T2.unics_id
WHERE T1.start_year = 2014

question: Find projects whose subject area is “Mathematics and Statistics”
query:
SELECT t1.title
FROM projects AS T1
         join project_subject_areas as psa on T1.unics_id = psa.project
         join subject_areas as sa on psa.subject_area = sa.code
WHERE sa.title = 'Mathematics and Statistics'

question: Show the acronym and subject area description of projects with subject area “Mathematics and Statistics”
query:
SELECT t1.acronym, sa.description
FROM projects AS T1
         join project_subject_areas as psa on T1.unics_id = psa.project
         join subject_areas as sa on psa.subject_area = sa.code
WHERE sa.title = 'Mathematics and Statistics'

question: Find all different topics of projects that ended in 2014
query:
SELECT distinct t.title
FROM projects AS T1
         join project_topics as pt on T1.unics_id = pt.project
         join topics as t on pt.topic = t.code
where t1.end_year = 2014

question: Find distinct titles of topics of projects that with end year 2014
query:
SELECT distinct t.title
FROM projects AS T1
         join project_topics as pt on T1.unics_id = pt.project
         join topics as t on pt.topic = t.code
where t1.end_year = 2014

question: Show the acronym of projects with a member from Greece
query:
Select p.acronym
from projects as p
         join project_members as pm on p.unics_id = pm.project
         join institutions as i on pm.institution_id = i.unics_id
         join countries as c on i.country_id = c.unics_id
where c.country_name = 'Greece'

question: Show names of institutions from France or Germany

         join countries as c on i.country_id = c.unics_id
where c.country_name = 'France' or c.country_name = 'Germany'

question: Show names of institutions which are not from France

question: Show the title of the project with the highest total cost
query:
Select p.title
from projects as p
where total_cost = (select max(p2.total_cost) from projects as p2)

question: Show the name of members in projects costing less than the average project cost.
query:
SELECT T1.member_name
FROM project_members AS T1
         JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.project = T2.unics_id
WHERE T2.total_cost < (SELECT AVG(T23.total_cost) FROM projects AS T23)

question: Find the id of projects with at least 100 members
query:
select p.unics_id
from projects as p
         join project_members as pm on p.unics_id = pm.project
group by p.unics_id
having count(p.unics_id) >= 100

question: Find the code and title of the funding scheme which funded the highest number of projects.
query:
select s.code, s.title
from funding_schemes as s
where s.code = (select s2.code
                 from funding_schemes as s2
                          join projects as p on s2.code = p.ec_fund_scheme
                 group by s2.code
                 order by count(*) desc
                 LIMIT 1)

question: Show the project title and member name where the member has a partner role

question: Show all names of institutions from France except institutions from the territorial region of Paris
query:
select i.institutions_name
from institutions as i
         join countries as c on c.unics_id = i.country_id
where country_name = 'France'
    except
select i.institutions_name
from institutions as i
         join countries as c on c.unics_id = i.country_id
         join eu_territorial_units as etu on i.geocode_regions_3 = etu.geocode_regions
where country_name = 'France'
  and etu.description = 'Paris'
